WEBVTT

1
00:02:16.040 --> 00:02:18.292
It's a question of ambition really.

2
00:02:19.335 --> 00:02:21.045
Let me rephrase that.

3
00:02:21.212 --> 00:02:23.464
It's a matter of limitation.

4
00:02:24.048 --> 00:02:26.634
And the importance of knowing yours.

5
00:02:27.676 --> 00:02:31.388
Your boss. Tama.
He had a reputation. yes.

6
00:02:31.555 --> 00:02:35.684
But he also knew where he stood.
understood how high he should climb.

7
00:02:35.851 --> 00:02:38.187
That's why Bangun
let him be the man he was.

8
00:02:46.237 --> 00:02:47.905
Don't mind them.

9
00:02:51.283 --> 00:02:53.327
I'm a reasonable man.

10
00:02:53.494 --> 00:02:55.621
Like you. I have ambitions.

11
00:02:57.039 --> 00:02:58.833
But you see. in this world of ours...

12
00:02:58.999 --> 00:03:01.877
it's really more of a
"one step at a time" kind of thing.

13
00:03:02.878 --> 00:03:06.215
And you should have been
some fucking steps away...

14
00:03:06.382 --> 00:03:09.218
from a meeting like this.

15
00:03:11.756 --> 00:03:12.756
Bangun will...

16
00:03:12.816 --> 00:03:14.306
Bangun is an old man!

17
00:03:19.395 --> 00:03:21.105
He's on his way out.

18
00:03:24.984 --> 00:03:26.652
I gave you a chance.

19
00:03:26.819 --> 00:03:28.612
You chose him.

20
00:03:34.869 --> 00:03:36.245
So...

21
00:03:37.037 --> 00:03:39.665
I guess this brings us back
full circle. ambition...

22
00:03:40.833 --> 00:03:42.126
and limitation.

23
00:03:43.043 --> 00:03:45.504
Bejo. Bejo!

24
00:03:45.671 --> 00:03:47.882
- Please don't do this.
- I already told you.

25
00:03:48.299 --> 00:03:50.676
- Don't worry.
- No. no!

26
00:03:50.843 --> 00:03:52.261
Don't. Bejo. wait!

27
00:04:31.550 --> 00:04:33.385
You called?

28
00:04:33.552 --> 00:04:34.970
Rama.

29
00:04:36.555 --> 00:04:37.973
I know who you are.

30
00:04:38.933 --> 00:04:40.309
My brother says...

31
00:04:40.476 --> 00:04:41.852
you're someone I can trust.

32
00:04:43.020 --> 00:04:45.397
He's right.

33
00:04:48.233 --> 00:04:50.194
They got you pretty bad.

34
00:04:53.572 --> 00:04:55.199
Yes. sir. they did.

35
00:04:57.701 --> 00:04:59.870
Take him through. get him treated.

36
00:05:07.294 --> 00:05:09.046
Be careful.

37
00:05:35.155 --> 00:05:38.033
No. wait! Stop!

38
00:05:38.200 --> 00:05:40.285
What the fuck?! No!

39
00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:49.920
- What the fuck was that?!
- It's okay. Just calm down.

40
00:05:50.087 --> 00:05:52.506
Take a seat. Sit.

41
00:06:07.271 --> 00:06:10.107
Take his jacket.
gloves and any official threads he has.

42
00:06:10.274 --> 00:06:12.651
Dump him far away from here.

43
00:06:12.943 --> 00:06:15.487
He'll float to shore by dawn.

44
00:06:15.738 --> 00:06:17.364
Yes. sir.

45
00:06:19.616 --> 00:06:21.243
Trust me.

46
00:06:21.410 --> 00:06:23.412
He would've never survived
until morning.

47
00:06:25.080 --> 00:06:29.209
This is the only way we can be sure
he won't say a word about you.

48
00:06:29.626 --> 00:06:30.627
About us.

49
00:06:32.254 --> 00:06:33.297
Us?

50
00:06:33.464 --> 00:06:37.468
I run a unit that weeds out
crooked cops like him.

51
00:06:38.260 --> 00:06:42.973
And I could do with someone like you
to help me dig out some more.

52
00:06:43.140 --> 00:06:45.225
We're a small division.

53
00:06:45.684 --> 00:06:48.937
But we're small for a reason. Trust.

54
00:06:49.980 --> 00:06:51.273
I have evidence.

55
00:06:51.440 --> 00:06:54.151
We could've made a case.
I could've testified.

56
00:06:54.401 --> 00:06:58.155
No. you have hearsay.
and a box of tapes.

57
00:06:59.573 --> 00:07:03.118
I've been down that road before.
All it does is cough up...

58
00:07:03.285 --> 00:07:06.497
a few more names to take the heat.
All foot soldiers just like him.

59
00:07:06.914 --> 00:07:09.750
No. if we're going to
clean up this city...

60
00:07:09.917 --> 00:07:14.046
we have to aim higher. All of them.

61
00:07:15.923 --> 00:07:19.551
Whether or not you like what happened
here today. they will come for you.

62
00:07:19.718 --> 00:07:21.845
They'll do anything to remove you
from the equation.

63
00:07:22.012 --> 00:07:23.889
If we don't act fast...

64
00:07:24.056 --> 00:07:26.058
you'll be gone.

65
00:07:26.225 --> 00:07:28.185
Your family too.

66
00:07:33.565 --> 00:07:35.442
But it doesn't have to be that way.

67
00:07:35.734 --> 00:07:38.612
Let's say we keep this internal.
If you keep your mouth shut...

68
00:07:38.779 --> 00:07:42.032
until everything is taken care of.
I can protect you.

69
00:07:43.033 --> 00:07:44.368
For you...

70
00:07:44.535 --> 00:07:48.122
<i>today never happened.
You were never here.</i>

71
00:07:48.288 --> 00:07:50.874
<i>In their eyes you're still a rookie
for fuck's sake.</i>

72
00:07:51.041 --> 00:07:54.962
<i>They won't even blink an eye
at one name missing from the report.</i>

73
00:08:04.638 --> 00:08:06.598
Is this all of them?

74
00:08:06.765 --> 00:08:08.976
All 18.

75
00:08:09.726 --> 00:08:11.645
No survivors.

76
00:08:23.532 --> 00:08:25.075
What do you think?

77
00:08:27.786 --> 00:08:28.787
Reza.

78
00:08:34.209 --> 00:08:35.878
I'll keep looking.

79
00:08:36.628 --> 00:08:38.839
I'll take care of it personally.

80
00:08:39.631 --> 00:08:41.300
You have to.

81
00:08:54.688 --> 00:08:56.732
What do you want'?

82
00:08:58.275 --> 00:09:01.028
I want you on my team.

83
00:09:01.195 --> 00:09:05.490
You'll be re-trained
until you have better skills.

84
00:09:05.657 --> 00:09:08.160
For the good...

85
00:09:08.327 --> 00:09:10.871
of this city. What do you say?

86
00:09:14.833 --> 00:09:17.377
No. Not interested.

87
00:09:18.212 --> 00:09:21.215
- Come again?
- Sir...

88
00:09:21.381 --> 00:09:22.799
with all due respect.

89
00:09:22.966 --> 00:09:26.220
I brought him in to do time. So
he could be brought to justice.

90
00:09:26.386 --> 00:09:29.348
And we put a bullet in him
to protect your life!

91
00:09:29.514 --> 00:09:32.643
There's no such thing as a clean
war in this world. Open your eyes!

92
00:09:32.809 --> 00:09:35.187
My eyes are wide open. sir!

93
00:09:35.354 --> 00:09:37.898
We may be after the same thing...

94
00:09:39.441 --> 00:09:42.486
but I'm not going to follow the
same path as you to get there.

95
00:10:33.078 --> 00:10:35.664
Who killed him?

96
00:10:35.831 --> 00:10:37.416
My brother.

97
00:10:37.582 --> 00:10:39.251
His name is Bejo.

98
00:10:39.418 --> 00:10:41.318
He's been on the up for some time now.

99
00:10:41.962 --> 00:10:44.464
I know the name.

100
00:10:44.631 --> 00:10:46.383
Rama...

101
00:10:47.634 --> 00:10:49.928
your brother had big enemies.

102
00:10:50.095 --> 00:10:54.641
But they're nothing
compared to what's coming for you.

103
00:10:54.808 --> 00:10:56.727
I can provide safety
for your wife and child.

104
00:10:56.893 --> 00:11:00.522
We can keep them out of reach.
But I need you.

105
00:11:00.689 --> 00:11:02.274
Right now...

106
00:11:02.441 --> 00:11:04.151
this city is carved up...

107
00:11:04.318 --> 00:11:06.611
between our local kingpin. Bangun...

108
00:11:06.778 --> 00:11:09.281
and the Goto family from Japan.

109
00:11:10.615 --> 00:11:13.368
Tama's job is to bribe everyone.

110
00:11:13.535 --> 00:11:16.872
And the police are being bribed
at his office so no one knows.

111
00:11:17.039 --> 00:11:19.791
If we get you close enough
to Bangun...

112
00:11:19.958 --> 00:11:23.211
then sure as fuck we can weed out
the rest of those crooked bastards.

113
00:11:23.378 --> 00:11:24.838
Rama...

114
00:11:26.423 --> 00:11:28.050
for this to end...

115
00:11:28.216 --> 00:11:29.968
I need those names.

116
00:11:30.135 --> 00:11:32.346
I need evidence that Reza...

117
00:11:32.512 --> 00:11:34.890
is connected to Bangun.

118
00:11:37.434 --> 00:11:38.602
So. what's the next step?

119
00:11:39.644 --> 00:11:41.688
Uco. Bangun's only child.

120
00:11:41.855 --> 00:11:43.899
He's serving time in prison.

121
00:11:44.816 --> 00:11:47.486
It's the perfect opportunity.
Get in. get close.

122
00:11:50.405 --> 00:11:51.823
Meaning?

123
00:11:52.616 --> 00:11:54.201
I have to arrest you.

124
00:11:57.162 --> 00:11:59.498
It will only be a few months.

125
00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:04.461
You can't know where I am.

126
00:12:06.463 --> 00:12:09.883
And I can't be seen anywhere near you
or Angga.

127
00:12:12.719 --> 00:12:14.513
But if I don't do this...

128
00:12:14.679 --> 00:12:17.182
I can't protect us this time.

129
00:12:18.141 --> 00:12:20.102
Please understand.

130
00:12:21.770 --> 00:12:23.772
This is the only choice I have left.

131
00:12:25.315 --> 00:12:27.275
<i>He's out of the hospital now. right?</i>

132
00:12:27.442 --> 00:12:29.486
<i>I heard he was discharged.</i>

133
00:12:29.653 --> 00:12:31.571
Shut your fucking mouth!

134
00:12:32.280 --> 00:12:34.116
You nod here.

135
00:12:34.866 --> 00:12:37.119
Yes or no. Do you understand me?

136
00:12:55.846 --> 00:12:56.847
So. what did he do?

137
00:12:58.640 --> 00:12:59.641
What did he do?

138
00:13:01.268 --> 00:13:03.103
Enough.

139
00:13:05.021 --> 00:13:06.648
I need more than that.

140
00:13:07.315 --> 00:13:09.526
He's the asshole son
of an asshole politician.

141
00:13:10.318 --> 00:13:12.446
Can't you just put me in. lock me up?

142
00:13:12.521 --> 00:13:14.101
Why does this kid have to bleed?

143
00:13:14.143 --> 00:13:17.742
His daddy is the reason
Uco is in prison.

144
00:13:17.909 --> 00:13:20.245
If we're talking earning credibility...

145
00:13:20.412 --> 00:13:22.664
doing this puts you
immediately on his radar.

146
00:13:22.831 --> 00:13:26.626
At the very least. it gives you
two something to talk about.

147
00:13:27.461 --> 00:13:29.379
If you really want me to beat him up...

148
00:13:29.546 --> 00:13:32.757
I mean really beat him up.
I need a better reason.

149
00:13:35.802 --> 00:13:40.474
He's also a major benefactor...

150
00:13:41.016 --> 00:13:42.809
for Bejo.

151
00:13:48.482 --> 00:13:49.608
Rama. listen...

152
00:13:50.901 --> 00:13:53.236
do enough to get inside...

153
00:13:53.403 --> 00:13:57.324
but not enough
to keep you there for good.

154
00:14:02.120 --> 00:14:03.121
Where is he?

155
00:19:01.544 --> 00:19:04.047
I believe Benny and his boys
introduced themselves yesterday?

156
00:19:04.964 --> 00:19:06.132
Which one is Benny?

157
00:19:07.550 --> 00:19:08.635
Him.

158
00:19:13.014 --> 00:19:15.809
Now while I'm in here.
Benny and his associates are with me.

159
00:19:15.975 --> 00:19:18.144
Oh. yeah? And who are you?

160
00:19:21.564 --> 00:19:23.358
You'll figure that out at some point.

161
00:19:23.525 --> 00:19:26.361
And when you do. maybe you'll show me
a little more fucking respect.

162
00:19:28.196 --> 00:19:30.448
But for now. I'll be tolerant.

163
00:19:34.911 --> 00:19:36.621
So. what does that mean?

164
00:19:37.372 --> 00:19:38.623
Want me to apologize?

165
00:19:39.332 --> 00:19:40.625
This?

166
00:19:41.918 --> 00:19:43.628
This is my "just in case."

167
00:19:44.504 --> 00:19:48.007
There's never enough walls
to cover your back.

168
00:19:48.174 --> 00:19:49.676
Even you.

169
00:19:49.843 --> 00:19:52.220
Especially after your little "display."

170
00:19:54.472 --> 00:19:56.850
I'm someone who can put walls up.

171
00:19:56.916 --> 00:19:59.385
I can cover your back
in any square inch of this place.

172
00:19:59.452 --> 00:20:01.621
You may not know who I am now.

173
00:20:01.688 --> 00:20:04.357
But when you do.
you'll realize how real my offer is.

174
00:20:04.524 --> 00:20:06.150
Join with us...

175
00:20:06.317 --> 00:20:08.570
and own this wing with me.

176
00:20:09.487 --> 00:20:11.739
We could use someone like you
fighting on our side.

177
00:20:14.367 --> 00:20:15.702
I'm flattered but...

178
00:20:15.869 --> 00:20:18.246
Just so you know. I hate rejections.

179
00:20:20.164 --> 00:20:21.875
With all due respect.

180
00:20:22.041 --> 00:20:25.003
I don't really like spending my time
acting tough in toilets.

181
00:20:25.295 --> 00:20:26.671
Excuse me.

182
00:20:26.838 --> 00:20:28.548
Listen...

183
00:20:29.549 --> 00:20:31.885
In here you'd be wise to pick a side.

184
00:20:32.510 --> 00:20:34.846
Loners don't tend to last long.

185
00:20:36.806 --> 00:20:38.266
Clearly.

186
00:21:13.551 --> 00:21:16.054
The warden tells me
you've got quite a group here.

187
00:21:17.096 --> 00:21:18.932
I got who I could.

188
00:21:19.098 --> 00:21:22.143
I'm working to get some of our guys
inside to cover your back.

189
00:21:22.310 --> 00:21:24.687
But until I do.
you got to keep a low profile.

190
00:21:24.854 --> 00:21:27.941
- You can't trust any of these fuckers.
- Low profile?

191
00:21:28.650 --> 00:21:29.984
I'm my father's son.

192
00:21:30.151 --> 00:21:33.071
That alone makes me a target here.

193
00:21:33.237 --> 00:21:36.866
All I can do is use
that to protect myself.

194
00:21:37.116 --> 00:21:39.869
Your job is to protect me here.

195
00:21:40.036 --> 00:21:43.164
It would make my job a lot easier
if you'd cool things down here.

196
00:21:43.331 --> 00:21:45.249
When was the last time
you did time. Eka?

197
00:21:46.584 --> 00:21:48.753
Keeping quiet is not an option.

198
00:21:48.920 --> 00:21:52.590
Unless I want to wake up every morning
with a broom up my ass.

199
00:21:58.221 --> 00:22:01.182
Rather than lecturing me.
find out about that guy.

200
00:22:02.100 --> 00:22:03.726
Why's he here?

201
00:22:04.143 --> 00:22:05.770
Him?

202
00:22:07.271 --> 00:22:10.441
He wheel-chaired your favorite
politician's kid in Fuazan's club.

203
00:22:11.150 --> 00:22:12.443
Not bad.

204
00:22:12.610 --> 00:22:14.654
His name's Yuda. He's from the sticks.

205
00:22:14.816 --> 00:22:15.816
He's a nobody.

206
00:22:15.866 --> 00:22:18.366
Well. that "nobody"...
took out 15 of my guys.

207
00:22:18.419 --> 00:22:20.198
So he can fight... so what?

208
00:22:20.326 --> 00:22:24.080
He's clean.
no connections on the outside.

209
00:22:43.391 --> 00:22:44.559
Who the fuck are you?

210
00:22:46.210 --> 00:22:48.230
I'm the guy gifting you
five years of my graft...

211
00:22:48.396 --> 00:22:50.231
just so you can say you belong.

212
00:22:50.398 --> 00:22:52.567
Since you walked in through that door...

213
00:22:52.734 --> 00:22:56.029
they've been eyeballing you. All
trying to get a feel for who you are.

214
00:22:57.196 --> 00:22:59.490
But by me sitting here...

215
00:23:00.241 --> 00:23:02.160
I just made you a somebody.

216
00:23:04.537 --> 00:23:07.248
You can thank me later.

217
00:23:07.415 --> 00:23:11.878
Oh. yeah. who do I thank
for the fucking three years I got?

218
00:23:13.713 --> 00:23:16.090
Bunawar said I'd be out in months...

219
00:23:16.257 --> 00:23:17.508
not years.

220
00:23:17.675 --> 00:23:19.592
Did you really think
that crook politician

221
00:23:19.634 --> 00:23:21.137
would stop at you being in here?

222
00:23:21.345 --> 00:23:23.222
That it would make things "even." Fair?

223
00:23:23.389 --> 00:23:25.141
No.

224
00:23:25.308 --> 00:23:29.020
No. You went after his son.
Be glad he didn't come after yours.

225
00:23:32.440 --> 00:23:33.941
I need you to talk to Bunawar...

226
00:23:35.610 --> 00:23:38.821
No. I'm just here to show my face.
And I did that already.

227
00:23:38.988 --> 00:23:41.074
Now you're on your own.

228
00:23:43.201 --> 00:23:45.912
Suck it up. don't fuck it up.

229
00:23:46.079 --> 00:23:50.291
I rely on you now
the same way you relied on me.

230
00:23:55.088 --> 00:23:57.298
Those bruises will heal.

231
00:32:18.590 --> 00:32:20.133
How does it feel?

232
00:32:20.300 --> 00:32:21.676
Different.

233
00:32:22.885 --> 00:32:24.679
- Here. give me that.
- No need.

234
00:32:24.846 --> 00:32:26.825
Just give it to me.
If I'd parked further

235
00:32:26.867 --> 00:32:28.600
away then. yeah.
carry it yourself.

236
00:32:28.766 --> 00:32:31.019
But this. this I got.

237
00:32:31.294 --> 00:32:34.330
- It's good to have you out.
- I appreciate what you did for me.

238
00:32:34.397 --> 00:32:36.416
You helped me a lot
while I was in there.

239
00:32:36.482 --> 00:32:38.985
Pass on my thanks to your father.

240
00:32:39.152 --> 00:32:41.029
You can do that yourself.

241
00:32:41.446 --> 00:32:42.947
We're going to his office.

242
00:32:43.114 --> 00:32:44.741
He wants to greet you personally.

243
00:32:44.907 --> 00:32:47.160
- He doesn't have to.
- Yeah. he does.

244
00:32:51.831 --> 00:32:53.374
Okay?

245
00:33:14.812 --> 00:33:17.357
Do you know of a man
goes by the name Bejo?

246
00:33:18.858 --> 00:33:20.318
Sounds familiar.

247
00:33:20.985 --> 00:33:24.322
Half-Arab kid. made a name for himself
when he took out Yudi's group.

248
00:33:25.114 --> 00:33:27.408
He's been making waves of late.

249
00:33:28.951 --> 00:33:31.287
Owns a few restaurants...

250
00:33:31.454 --> 00:33:34.248
takes care of problems
for high-profile clients.

251
00:33:34.957 --> 00:33:37.835
The kind that can't afford
to carry a spotlight.

252
00:33:40.046 --> 00:33:42.131
I know him. came to me way back...

253
00:33:42.298 --> 00:33:45.218
wanting collateral to set up shop.

254
00:33:46.886 --> 00:33:49.972
I'm getting rumors that
he's looking to expand his operations.

255
00:33:51.057 --> 00:33:52.517
Where?

256
00:33:52.684 --> 00:33:54.394
That's where the rumors stop.

257
00:33:54.977 --> 00:33:57.397
But it will be one of ours.

258
00:34:04.529 --> 00:34:06.030
Yes. that's right.

259
00:34:06.197 --> 00:34:09.492
I'm sorry. sir. He cannot
